<!-- WORKFLOW -->
<section id="workflow" class="section active">
  <div class="section-label">How it works</div>
  <div class="section-title">System Workflow</div>
  <div class="section-sub">Five stages that transform a voluntary check-in into meaningful, private support ‚Äî without surveillance or judgment.</div>
  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step v-green">
      <div class="step-left"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-connector"></div></div>
      <div class="step-body"><div class="step-card">
        <h3>Routine Wellbeing Check (Fortnightly)</h3>
        <p>Employees voluntarily take a short emotional wellbeing assessment every two weeks, covering emotional exhaustion, motivation, work satisfaction, and overwhelm levels.</p>
        <div class="step-tags"><span class="tag tag-green">Voluntary</span><span class="tag tag-green">Fortnightly</span><span class="tag tag-green">Anonymous</span></div>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="step v-blue">
      <div class="step-left"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-connector"></div></div>
      <div class="step-body"><div class="step-card">
        <h3>Multi-Signal Support Layer</h3>
        <p>Optional behavioral indicators (check-in consistency) and anonymous peer wellbeing concerns are gathered as supportive context ‚Äî never as surveillance evidence.</p>
        <div class="step-tags"><span class="tag tag-blue">Behavioral Trends</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Peer Signals</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Support-Only</span></div>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="step v-amber">
      <div class="step-left"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-connector"></div></div>
      <div class="step-body"><div class="step-card">
        <h3>Follow-Up Reflective Test</h3>
        <p>If Medium or High risk is detected, a second short reflective test is offered after a gap ‚Äî confirming persistence of stress and preventing false positives from one-time emotional dips.</p>
        <div class="step-tags"><span class="tag tag-amber">Triggered on Medium/High</span><span class="tag tag-amber">Short Gap</span><span class="tag tag-amber">Prevents Overreaction</span></div>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="step v-amber">
      <div class="step-left"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-connector"></div></div>
      <div class="step-body"><div class="step-card">
        <h3>Persistence Evaluation</h3>
        <p>The AI compares Test 1, Test 2, behavioral trends, and peer signals to determine whether concern is temporary, moderate, or persistent ‚Äî before any action is recommended.</p>
        <div class="step-tags"><span class="tag tag-amber">Trend-Based</span><span class="tag tag-amber">Multi-Source</span><span class="tag tag-amber">No Labels</span></div>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="step v-red">
      <div class="step-left"><div class="step-num">5</div><div class="step-connector"></div></div>
      <div class="step-body"><div class="step-card">
        <h3>Counsellor Support (Optional)</h3>
        <p>If risk persists, the system gently asks: "Would you like to speak with a counsellor?" Outreach is optional, private, and entirely support-focused. No data is shared with managers, performance teams, or HR.</p>
        <div class="step-tags"><span class="tag tag-red">Optional</span><span class="tag tag-red">Private</span><span class="tag tag-red">Not HR-Linked</span><span class="tag tag-red">Counsellor Only</span></div>
      </div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

