<!-- ETHICS -->
<section id="ethics" class="section">
  <div class="section-label">Design principles</div>
  <div class="section-title">Ethical Architecture</div>
  <div class="section-sub">Every design decision was guided by one question: <em>"Does this protect the employee?"</em></div>
  <div class="ethics-grid" id="ethicsGrid">
    <div class="ethics-card"><span class="ethics-icon">ü§ù</span><h4>Voluntary Participation</h4><p>No employee is required to use the system. Engagement is always opt-in, ensuring trust is never coerced.</p></div>
    <div class="ethics-card"><span class="ethics-icon">üîí</span><h4>Privacy-First Architecture</h4><p>Data is not accessible to managers, performance teams, or HR. Confidentiality is structural, not just promised.</p></div>
    <div class="ethics-card"><span class="ethics-icon">üö´</span><h4>No Performance Linkage</h4><p>Wellbeing data is never used in appraisals, promotions, or disciplinary processes ‚Äî by design, not just policy.</p></div>
    <div class="ethics-card"><span class="ethics-icon">üß†</span><h4>No AI Diagnosis</h4><p>The system identifies "wellbeing signals," not clinical conditions. It never labels or diagnoses employees.</p></div>
    <div class="ethics-card"><span class="ethics-icon">üß≠</span><h4>AI Suggests ‚Äî Humans Decide</h4><p>All recommendations are suggestions. The employee retains full autonomy over whether to act or decline.</p></div>
    <div class="ethics-card"><span class="ethics-icon">üìà</span><h4>Trend-Based, Not Event-Based</h4><p>Patterns over time trigger consideration ‚Äî never a single emotional moment, preventing stigma around temporary hardship.</p></div>
    <div class="ethics-card"><span class="ethics-icon">üë§</span><h4>Peer Input is Anonymous</h4><p>Peer concerns are anonymous and weighted lightly. They add context but can never alone trigger any action.</p></div>
    <div class="ethics-card"><span class="ethics-icon">üå±</span><h4>Support Continuity</h4><p>Post-intervention, the system monitors recovery trends ‚Äî ensuring support doesn't end the moment someone accepts help.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- OUTCOMES -->
<section id="outcomes" class="section">
  <div class="section-label">Decision framework</div>
  <div class="section-title">Persistence Evaluation Outcomes</div>
  <div class="section-sub">After combining signals from both tests, behavioral data, and peer concerns, the AI determines one of four outcomes ‚Äî each with a proportionate response.</div>
  <table class="outcomes-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Risk Pattern</th><th>AI Assessment</th><th>System Response</th><th>Escalation?</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-green">Low</span></td><td>Temporary emotional dip; no cross-test persistence</td><td>Self-help resources (articles, breathing exercises, mindfulness tools)</td><td>None</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-amber">Moderate</span></td><td>Partial persistence; signals present but inconsistent</td><td>Monitor over next cycle; optional peer support access</td><td>Watch only</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-red">Persistent</span></td><td>Cross-test consistency; behavioral + peer signals confirmed</td><td>Gentle, private counsellor suggestion via employee's own interface</td><td>Counsellor only</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-purple">Crisis</span></td><td>Extreme distress pattern detected</td><td>Urgent support suggestion with full confidentiality maintained</td><td>Immediate private support</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <div class="info-strip"><strong>Key principle:</strong> A single signal ‚Äî one check-in, one peer concern, one bad day ‚Äî <em>never</em> triggers intervention. Only persistent, multi-source patterns cross the threshold for a counsellor suggestion.</div>
</section>

